Pre-Game Insights: India is the only unbeaten team in the tournament with five wins in as many matches.
England has only one win from five games and is hanging by a thread near the bottom of the points table.
India's key to success is their strong start, with Rohit Sharma setting the tone in the powerplay and Jasprit Bumrah having an impressive economy of 2.90 in the first ten overs.
Mohammed Shami picked up a five-wicket haul in his first match at this World Cup.
England seems to have already tried all 15 players in the original squad, left out their vice-captain for three out of five games, and played with no care in the world, but nothing has worked.
Others: India won by 100 runs, with England being dismissed for 129 in 34.5 overs.
